Took me a bit to get going today. My discipline has a tendency to talk shit to me from time to time 😂

I think we all have days where we feel like that and in my opinion, it’s a good thing. Motivation can be fleeting, so in those moments of “…I ain’t feeling this…” I ask myself one question: 

Why am I doing this? 

Answer always boils down to the same thing: I’m doing this for Me. 

It isn’t about comparison, competition or being better than anyone else. I compete against 1 man only….Me. 

Everyday. 

So in those moments of doubt or “I’ll do it tomorrow”… push yourself. Challenge yourself. Be yourself and above all else…

Do it for yourself.

After a near 30 hr travel day, I’m finally home. Sitting here jet lagged and eating TimTams, I have some time to reflect on an incredible trip to Australia for @worldserieswrestling 🙌🏻

I was challenged creatively, trusted, given the ball and got to work alongside and headline with some of the best talent on the planet today… I loved every damn second of it. 

Wrestling was FUN. 

Everyone, from wrestlers to production crew, to the wild fans themselves, this was a true team effort and one of the finest tours and companies I’ve ever had the pleasure of being apart of. I don’t throw around praise lightly but I’ll be the first one to shout from the rooftops when professionalism is top notch. 

To everyone who joined us on this tour, fans and wrestlers alike, the pleasure was all mine. Thank you for having me Australia. I love you all. 

Let’s do it again soon 🇦🇺❤️

Episode 18 with @aew star @theshawnspears has dropped!

Available on all podcast platforms - Apple, Spotify, Google, & YouTube. 

Codydeaner.com/podcast

***

Cody Deaner sits down with current AEW star Shawn Spears (formerly known as @wwenxt superstar Tye Dillinger). Cody and Shawn have been friends for over two decades. They sit down for a very personal conversation discussing their lives and lessons they've learned in their two different journeys in the wrestling business.
Shawn discusses a variety of things in Part 1 of this 2 part conversation, such as:

- how being a new dad has changed his perspective on his wrestling career and time in All Elite Wrestling

- when you start wrestling, you're signing up for the "maybes"

- the importance of having a source of happiness outside the wrestling business

- having a back up plan vs. putting all your eggs in one basket

- what his parents thought when he started wrestling school

- how @theericyoungig became his first true mentor in wrestling

- how life on the indies was not a "struggle" to him prior to his @wwe tryout experience in 2006

Shawn currently runs a wrestling school with former WWE Superstar @mmmgorgeous Tyler Breeze. You can learn all about @flatbackstraining at https://www.flatbackswrestlingschool.com/

It’s not about who you know. It’s about who you know & who is willing to vouch for you.

Shawn Spears explains how CM Punk was the reason he re-signed and got a 2nd chance with the @wwe 

Full episode on Apple, Spotify, & YouTube: CodyDeaner.com/podcast
